Virgin Atlantic flight VS44 from Las Vegas to Gatwick was delayed by 33 hours on Easter Monday . 
  Passengers were told there was a problem with the plane's rudder and taken to the Tropicana Las Vegas hotel . 
  The flight finally took off from the airport at 4am on Wednesday morning . 
  Some passengers are considering legal action against the airline . 
  Virgin Atlantic said the flight was delayed because of a technical fault . 
 